reviewText: Love the Maze!  Great old time B&W mood lighting!

This is a movie I have been wanting for years. It costs a little too much, but I was happy to pay it and get this movie. Just remember it will not play on us dvd players. You must have an international player.
The movie is OK for its time but I didn't get the crocker part it looks a home made copy of only the maze but that's OK it make a good part of my old SciFi collection

This is like the anvil you were happy with before you dropped it on your foot. Did L'Atelier 13, the Spanish distributor, think the nice booklet enclosed in the case would make us ignore the contrast build up and resultant sub-par quality? Now the only enjoyment will be to find a translator because the booklet mentions 16mm and 35mm and could explain the miserable picture quality. There is at least one other version out there. Keep looking, it's from Resurrectionvideo.com. 3D artwork on the cover. It's better if not pure.
